    "midrange-human-results.json": "4 PROJECTION clones (M01-M04) scored 0-5/100 — overreacted/tailwind/vercel/stripe. M03 (overreacted) + M01 (tailwind) have LIVE local clone_pages (341, 268) and are the two pairs the resolution-win proof runs on; M02/M04 are screenshot-only.",
    "_honesty": "ALL existing human scores cluster 0-6/100 (every labeled pair is a BROKEN clone — the user audited the grader's own 'best' outputs and found them worthless). The corpus therefore has NO mid/high human anchors yet. Calibrating tolerances on a 0-6 band alone fits only the floor; the HOLDOUT split (and future GOOD clones) MUST be human-scored to anchor the upper range. This gap is flagged on every HOLDOUT entry."
